    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-11-27T11:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-11-27T11:29:00-05:00" n="752"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.61351/307: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-11-27T11:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1921—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>142. For Mr. Sumner Welles.<note n="1" xml:id="d752fn1">Chief of the Division of
                        Latin American Affairs.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I think President Zayas in substantial accord with you, has a proposition to
                    abolish Sugar Finance Commission at once rather than wait until February 1st as
                    originally contemplated. At our last conference it [was] suggested [that] it
                    would be advisable before <pb facs="0931" n="807" xml:id="pg_807"/> issuing a
                    decree of this character to consult the owners of the carryover sugar. I have
                    for several days contemplated that a decree abolishing said Commission would be
                    issued at an early date with the approval of said owners and the consent of both
                    Governments.</p>
                <p>Respecting the tariff, public opinion here continues chaotic but an effort is
                    being made to secure a study and report upon an <hi rend="italic">ad
                        valorcm</hi> tariff. Have held important conferences in the last few days
                    [in] supreme effort to consolidate Cuban public opinion in favor of the <hi
                        rend="italic">ad valorem</hi> duty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
